        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-08-06 14:30:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFunctionally, the changes look correct.\n\nI think we can use the terms:  identity bearing, for the existing case, and non-identity bearing for the case you're calling server side.  Strange as it may seem, an non-identity bearing cert can be used on the client side, and vice versa.\n\n\nAlso, I have stronger concern about the complexity of the requestCertFunctional method.  The original complexity had already been high.  And this code change adds more.  (e.g., more conditions)\n\nI raise this only because the security concern is critical.  Its not a matter of aesthetic.  If the code is left like this, then future intended change to once case may inadvertently change the other.\n\nI'd like to see a stronger isolation of the two cases, if possible.  Can there be different versions of requestCert for each case?  Maybe the validation and security checks can be extracted as methods and reused by either case?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
